summary:
▪ 15+ years of international professional experience providing technical assistance in the area of justice reform and child protection. In particular, has experience working on the following issues: criminal justice; juvenile justice; violence against children; child-friendly procedures and processes for child victims of crime; anti-trafficking. 
▪ Experience working in or consulting for OSCE ODIHR, UNICEF, EU FWC projects, The International Institute for Justice and the Rule of Law, OSCE Field Operations, Coimbra University (EU Prevention of and Fight Against Crime (ISEC)-funded anti-trafficking project), etc.
▪ Experience with long-term technical assistance involving a major capacity-building component.
▪Ample experience in training development and delivery.
▪ Experience conducting evaluations.
▪ Extensive knowledge of the Eastern and South-East Europe, Central Asia, Middle East and South Caucasus regions.
▪ Experience in projects with a budget of EUR 200,000 and higher.
▪ Native-level proficiency in English and Russian.  Working knowledge of Spanish and Polish.
